      <h1 class="hero-title" id="page-title" style="font-size:clamp(28px,4.5vw,50px);">What is sports technology?</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Sports technology is the application of technology to enhance, analyse, commercialise, and grow sport - from elite performance analysis to fan engagement platforms to medical diagnostics for athletes.</p>
      <p class="hero-note">A reference for sport organisations, technology companies, investors, and founders exploring the African sports tech landscape.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#how-structured" class="btn btn-primary">See how the sector is structured</a>
        <a href="/ecosystem/" class="btn btn-outline">African ecosystem →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Definition -->
<section class="section section--white" aria-labelledby="definition-title">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">The sector</span>
      <h2 class="section-title" id="definition-title">Sports technology is broad - and growing</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>
      <p class="section-lead">The term covers any technology applied to sport - whether that improves how athletes train and recover, how fans engage with their sport, how organisations manage their operations, or how the business of sport generates revenue. It spans software, hardware, data, materials science, and health technology.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card card--gold-top reveal">
        <h3>Performance technology</h3>
        <p>Tools that enhance athlete training, recovery, and performance - wearables, biomechanics analysis, nutrition tracking, and injury prevention systems.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card card--gold-top reveal">
        <h3>Business of sport</h3>
        <p>Technology supporting the commercial side of sport - fan engagement platforms, media and broadcasting tools, ticketing, e-sports, fantasy, and venue operations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card card--gold-top reveal">
        <h3>Infrastructure technology</h3>
        <p>The enabling layer - connectivity, data infrastructure, cloud platforms, and the hardware and sensors that underpin the rest of the sector.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

