<!-- Africa context -->
<section class="section section--white" aria-labelledby="africa-title">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Sports technology in Africa</span>
      <h2 class="section-title" id="africa-title">A market with significant momentum</h2>
      <div class="section-divider section-divider--center"></div>
      <p class="section-lead" style="margin:0 auto;">Sports technology activity in Africa is concentrated primarily in South Africa, with growing ecosystems developing across the continent. AfricanSTN focuses on South Africa as its operational base, with a continental perspective as the platform grows.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2 reveal" style="gap:32px;align-items:start;">
      <div>
        <div class="card card--gold-top">
          <h3>South Africa</h3>
          <p>The most mature sports tech market on the continent. Strong commercial sport infrastructure across football, rugby, and cricket, a developed regulatory environment including POPIA, and an active technology startup ecosystem make South Africa the natural starting point for any company entering African sport.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">
        <div class="card card--gold-top" style="padding:20px;">
          <h3 style="font-size:15px;">Continental scope</h3>
          <p>AfricanSTN takes a continental view of the sports tech landscape - tracking activity, companies, and developments across all 54 African countries as the platform develops.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card card--gold-top" style="padding:20px;">
          <h3 style="font-size:15px;">Regulatory infrastructure</h3>
          <p>South Africa's POPIA framework is among the most advanced data protection regimes on the continent, creating both compliance obligations and market confidence for international operators.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

